  Paste this block into your GEMINI.md (project root, or ~/.gemini/GEMINI.md for all projects).
  It tells Gemini CLI WHEN and HOW to offload cheap/bulk work to cheapskate via the run_task MCP
  tool. Requires the cheapskate MCP server registered (see settings.snippet.json in this folder).
-->

## Token-saving offload to cheapskate

A cheapskate MCP server is registered. It gives you two tools:

- `run_task(task_type, criteria, payload)`: routes ONE subtask to the cheapest model that clears
  the acceptance criteria (local first, cloud only on escalation), verifies and repairs the result,
  and returns `route` (local|cloud|refused), `ok`, `retries`, `escalated`, and `output`.
- `econ_report(month?)`: the monthly savings receipt.

**Offload the bulk work; keep your tokens for judgement.** When a subtask is high-volume and
low-judgement, call `run_task` with explicit acceptance criteria instead of doing it yourself:

- drafting (commit messages, docstrings, changelog entries, boilerplate prose)
- classification and labeling
- extraction (fields/values out of a blob into a shape)
- summarization of long files or logs
- first-pass code review (you then sanity-check the findings)
- boilerplate code (repetitive scaffolding, test stubs)

Reserve your own reasoning for architecture, planning, final review, and synthesis.

**Always verify.** A `run_task` result is a draft. Check `output` against the `criteria` you sent
before you use it. If `ok` is false or `route` is `refused`, discard it.

**Never offload these.** `financial`, `legal`, `medical`, and `credentials` are `never_local` and
cheapskate refuses them by design. Never route money, legal, medical, or secret-handling work
through `run_task` to save tokens; do it yourself.

### Examples

Draft a commit message:

```
run_task(
  task_type="draft",
  criteria="Imperative subject under 72 chars, blank line, then 2-4 bullets of what changed and why. No emojis.",
  payload="<git diff --staged output>"
)
```

Extract structured fields from text:

```
run_task(
  task_type="extract",
  criteria="Return JSON with keys name, email, company. Use null for any field not present. Output only the JSON object.",
  payload="<the raw text blob>"
)
```
